            <td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">The instability index is a length-scaled measure of the occurrence of all dipeptides in a protein sequence. Guruprasad and colleagues found a correlation between this measure and protein stability: in general, stable proteins have instability indices smaller than 40.</td>
