            <td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Estimates of <italic>in vivo</italic> half-life for proteolysis of proteins in prokaryotes can be made by the N-end rule. This considers the presence of a destabilizing N-terminal residue that provides an N-degron degradation signal.</td>
