            <td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">The revised WilkinsonâHarrison statistical solubility model depends on two parameters: the fraction of residues with a high index for forming turns and the approximate average charge of the protein <italic>in vivo</italic>. This model has been shown to be useful in the selection of proteins with high solubility.</td>
